i>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Pass types:</strong> </p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Restricted Pass</strong> - our cheapest pass but <strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">can't</span></strong> be used over <em>peak dates*</em></li>\n<li><strong>Unrestricted Pass - </strong>enjoy skiing any time in the season <strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">including</span></strong> <em>peak dates*</em></li>\n<li><strong>EPIC Pass - </strong>valid for unlimited access to skiing throughout the season including peak dates and is the best option for those wanting to ski 11 days or more</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>*</strong><em>Peak dates - </em>if you wish to ski on the dates below, you will need to purchase an <strong>unrestricted pass</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>26 Dec - 31 Dec 2024</li>\n<li>18 Jan 2025 </li>\n<li>15 Feb - 16 Feb 2025</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>All passes are <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">non-refundable</span> and <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">no changes</span> can be made after purchase. Lift passes must be paid for in full at the time of booking.</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Prices and supplements are correct at time of publishing but may vary up or down; correct prices will be advised at the time of booking.</strong></p>"
